[1] Brazil (Bahia)
Date: Fri 14 Aug 2009
Source: UOL.com [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www2.uol.com.br/aregiao/2009/08/entry_353.html>


During the period between 16 Jul-12 Aug [2009], Itabuna recorded a
suspected DHF death and 101 new cases of dengue, showing that the
disease continues to threaten the city. The Public [Works?] Ministry
has stated that its recommended actions have been ignored by city
hall, such as the cleaning of all canals of the city and local
[vector control] fighting in neighborhoods with high infestation of
the mosquito _Aedes aegypti_.

In 2009, Itabuna has had the greatest dengue epidemic in its history,
with more the 13 000 cases of this disease, as well as 8 confirmed
[dengue] fatalities and 4 [additional fatal cases] awaiting
confirmation by the Central Laboratory in Salvador. And there are
still 4 months to go until the end of 2009.

--
